				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Couple of noob questions<a name="24069"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 26 04 11:33 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I just started playing EQ about 3 weeks ago - so far I've only played a bard and nearly all of that solo. I choose a bard mostly for the mix of soloing ability and desirablity in groups. Just upgraded to LDON, but no groups so far - I rarely see more than a couple of sub 40 toons lfg on Vazelle and my friends who play are all have multiple 65's and are raiding mostly. Not that the lack of grouping is such a bad thing - I'm a refugee from another game where I ran a 600+ toon guild for 2 years - I'm sorta enjoying the quiet.
<br />

<br />
Im right now lvl 32 and kiting Cougars in Iceclad for fun and profit. I've mixed melee into leveling enough to have 1hs, dual, off and def all 130+. I'm about to take a break and do some afk instrument training to bring those skills up. 
<br />

<br />
First question: What is a good (safe) way to bring up my other neglected skills - my other weapon (pierce, 1hb) skills are below 10 and my thief-type skills are just as bad. I understand people look to bards to take on the sense/disarm/pick tasks in groups. Am I just plain screwed from not grouping?
<br />

<br />
Second question: Apart from ignoring people complaining about me not keeping up mana in a group (see.. I read the boards) what should my grouping role be - should I load multiple spell sets for different group make ups? Any good guides on grouping roles out there I should be reading?
<br />

<br />
Thanks in advance for any responses or flames. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
CL</span></td>
