				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Couple of noob questions<a name="24155"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 26 04 5:29 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>To the First question - what I did was make a hotkey as follows
<br />

<br />
/stopsong
<br />
/cast 1-8
<br />
/do 1
<br />
/do 2
<br />
/do 3
<br />

<br />
what this does is the allow u to work on your abilities as u run around.  My abilities are set as 1) Forage, 2) Sense Traps 3) Disarm Traps [yes u get skill ups even if u have not found a trap].  I have maxed out my sense traps and have put in Tracking.  I just dinged 36 and have a tracking of 88.
<br />

<br />

<br />
As for the Second Question -  that is a bit more tuff to answer since we as bards are the Jack-of-all-Trades and a master of none (my humility bleeding through) we fill in for what ever the Group does not have.  But a rule of thumb the melee will want haste, casters will want mana, mez as either primary or secondary CC.  After that depends on what u want to do Chant or DS for extra DPS, Snare/Slow so the mob doesnt run and chain agro the dungeon, Lull for if u r pulling (they like us pulling).  The list goes on and the options just get bigger as u level.
<br />

<br />
P.S. Thank u EQDiva for the info on the Hotkeys  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" /></span></td>
