				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Couple of noob questions<a name="24161"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 26 04 5:51 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>For offensive Weapon skills, Snare-Fearing is great.  Get a Dex buff before you head out, if you can.  The mountain Giant Fort in Frontier Mountains might be a good place for this at your level.  (maybe a bit low...)  Dire Wolves in GD or Iceclad might be good.
<br />

<br />
You want an outdoor zone with lots of room to do fear snaring.
<br />

<br />
Defense skill is another tough problem.  Your best answer, the one I give people, is to Pull and do Crowd Control (mezzing and charming adds) for groups.  It sounds like Vazaelle is pretty barren of lowbie grouping opportunities though...  There are some gimmicky ways to raise defense, but you probably aren't high enough to use those yet.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
