				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Couple of noob questions<a name="26307"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 9 04 4:11 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>firstly, get agi buff and go duel a pet class (prefered with the /pet hold AA) let the pet beat you up, but before you die, have its master call it back, heal up rinse and repeat.
<br />

<br />
you you do get skillups on fighting pets
<br />

<br />
you could combine it with the 1HB and piercing trainging, you can hit the pet and get skillups on that as well.
<br />

<br />
best class to do this with is a shaman, as he will be able to buff you up, haste, regen and heal are there (and there pets dont hit too hard <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" />)
<br />

<br />
to your second question, I am the opposite, I group constantly, I am wanted, I get tells when I am in already grouped to know if I got a spot in my group <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-11.gif" border="0" alt="Cool" hspace="2" />
<br />
and for those who think grouping is slower, it might be a bit, but with a bard added to a DPS group mobs go down so fast i need to bring 3 or more to the group each time to keep them busy
